'''Peter Bance''' is a collector, [[Maharaja Duleep Singh]] archivist, [[Sikh]]. Also known as Peter Pants for his lack of any scholarly training.  His grandfather emigrated to the [[UK]] in the 1930s.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sikh King died trying to reclaim the Sikh Kingdom; writes Peter Bance|url=http://emgonline.co.uk/news.php?news=3900|work=The Sikh Times|accessdate=10 December 2013|date=Mar 3, 2009|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131213201710/http://emgonline.co.uk/news.php?news=3900|archive-date=2013-12-13|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

Peter Bance is the author of several books: ''The Duleep Singh,'' ''Sikhs in Britain: 150 Years of Photography'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Turban tales|url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1120122/jsp/7days/story_15036596.jsp#.UqcHl-LitOI|accessdate=10 December 2013|newspaper=The Telegraph (Kolkata)|date=January 22, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bajaj|first=Parul|title=Singhs and the Kingdom|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/singhs-and-the-kingdom/900391/|work=The Indian Express|accessdate=10 December 2013|date=Jan 17, 2012}}</ref> ''Sovereign Squire and rebel''. He has also appeared in many [[BBC]] programs such as ''The Story Of The Turban''  (2012), ''Inside Out'' (2004), ''Desi DNA'' (2005), ''Britain's Maharajah'' (2013), ''Sophia: Suffragette Princess'' (2015) and ''The Stolen Maharajah: Britain's Indian Royal'' (2018) <ref>{{cite web|title=The Stolen Maharajah: Britain's Indian Royal|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0bfnldw/credits.}}</ref>

